       #include <dshm.h>

       size_t    dshm_minmapsize  (size_t  buffer_size,  unsigned
       long max_mappings);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       dshm_minmapsize returns the minimum map size  required  to
       support  a  given number of concurrent mappings of a given
       buffer size on the current machine.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       dshm_minmapsize returns the minimum map size, in bytes

       If dshm_minmapsize returns size_t -1, an  error  occurred.
       errno is set to identify the error.

   EErrrroorrss
       In  the  following  conditions,  dshm_minmapsize fails and
       sets  errno  to:  buffer_size  is  not  a  power   of   2.
       buffer_size is greater than DSHM_MAX_BUFFER_SIZE.  DSHM is
       not supported.  The required map  size  cannot  fit  in  a
       size_t

